<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFE4FFE8E292A2F0CFE174DA" bold="true" box="[151,417,150,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">
<typeStatus id="FA64883AFFE4FFE8E292A2F0CE9274DA" box="[151,210,150,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Type</typeStatus>
and only species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFE4FFE8E3ADA2F0CD0A74DA" authority="Scudder, 1890" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1890" box="[424,842,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Tribochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vetuscula">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFE4FFE8E3ADA2F0CCE074DA" box="[424,672,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Tribochrysa vetuscula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFE4FFE8E0A2A2F0CD0A74DA" author="Scudder, S. H." box="[679,842,150,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" pagination="1 - 734" refId="ref25710" refString="Scudder, S. H. (1890) The Tertiary insects of North America. Report of the United States Geological Survey of the Territories, 13, 1 - 734, 28 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 44698" type="journal article" year="1890">Scudder, 1890</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25603698FFE4FFE8E2C2A2DCCB0F75E3" blockId="10.[151,1437,150,788]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFE4FFE8E2C2A2DCCFF774BE" bold="true" box="[199,439,186,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Emended diagnosis.</emphasis>
May be distinguished from other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFE4FFE8E1B5A2DCCA2174BE" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1910" box="[944,1121,186,212]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Nothochrysinae">Nothochrysinae</taxonomicName>
by a combination of: Forewing: (1) M forked far distad origin of RP (shared with 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFE4FFE8E101A2B8CDEC7492" authorityName="Adams" authorityYear="1967" box="[772,940,222,248]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Archaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFE4FFE8E101A2B8CDEC7492" box="[772,940,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Archaeochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) [other genera: proximad to slightly distad]; (2) one crossvein between RA, RP proximad 1r-m absent [
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFE4FFE8E12FA364CD927576" authorityName="Adams" authorityYear="1967" box="[810,978,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Archaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
